<br>
I've hunted sharks for over an hour at a time. I've done Kedge Keep. I've helped a shaman with the Erud's Crossing (i.e. underwater) portion of his epic quest. Never has my pet been the slightest bit fazed by being underwater.<br>
<br>
Shaman pets *do* drown if they do not receive an Enduring Breath spell. But then, they are animals, and they do sit around panting a lot (hence, they breathe).<br>
<br>
The problem in Qeynos Catacombs would be one of pathing, not of drowning. If the &quot;railroad tracks&quot; in the water portion are different from the land portion, it can be a little tricky to get your pet back up next to your side. He hasn't drowned, he's just gotten lost. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxymryk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xymryk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#333333>(10/30/01 5:40:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=788.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hrm? Drowning?</span><hr size=1> Down in the Qeynos Catacombs your right, I don't think the pet drowns.  But something definately happens to them.  If my pet went over the side into the water chasing cubert he would usually be gone for good.  Not just lost but the &quot;You Don't have a pet to command&quot; kind of gone.  I always figured that it driffted down to a zone line and got poofed, but I don't know what happend to it.<br>
<br>
Another good and easy to do quest as a teen-ager is kill bandits in South Karana and turn in their sashes until you become Amiable to the temple of Rodcet Nife.  This should be profitable and make you experience.  <br>
<br>
After you become amiable, walk to Surefall Glade, and get the nitrates potion from the General.  Then look for a port to Steamfront.  Take the Nitrates potion to the zoo Keeper in Ak'Anon under the city and he will give you a potion of regurgetronics.  (Sp).  Take the potion of regurgetronics to Frosty (The dog) in West Karana and he will give you the fish for the band of Rodcet Nife.  You can just have a friend kill a fish for you and save all the walking, but if you like to roll play this really is a much better way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uedano.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edano</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Limey Magician</span><br>  Posts: 186<br> <font color=#333333>(11/1/01 6:00:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=788.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://website.lineone.net/~rexz/moo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question for low level mage</span><hr size=1> The problem in Qeynos Catacombs is that when Cubert is low on health he runs.  And he runs the same way each time.  And if you let him run this way for a few seconds, he will jump (flop?) off the sidewalk and into the water and then go down a well.  At a certain point in the well your pet will poof.  I cant remember if Cubert also disappears (this was 45 levels ago <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), but having no pet anywhere is a bad thing. <p><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td><i